@ondrejmirtes is it still planned? Im currently facing the same issue.

While my path on the phpstan environment (docker) is `/app/file.php` my host path is `/Users/simonmarx/project/file.php`.

As mentioned above, something like str_replace or preg_replace would also suffice for my case.

It looks like providing the type hint for the `$accounts` solves the issue, although the dumped type of `$accounts` doesn't change.

```php
    /**
     * @param list<string> $ids
     *
     * @return list<Account>
     */
    private function accounts(array $ids): array
    {
        /** @var list<Account|null> $accounts */
        $accounts = array_map(fn (string $id): ?Account => $this->accounts->find($id), $ids);

        Assert::allNotNull($accounts);

        return $accounts;
    }
```
